      "createdAt": "2023-03-21T21:25:18.577Z",
      "author": "mark.anley (Green Llamas Consulting)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hi <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/fahad_s\">@Fahad_S</a> - its possible Zapier might be seeing the Column ID vs what you have named it.  If you enable Developer mode in <a href=\"https://support.monday.com/hc/en-us/articles/360002138760-Testing-beta-features-with-monday-labs\">monday.labs</a> you can see the column ID in the settings of the column:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/e/1/e11b41e1acc1e0fd5e63116fa11ca6689c42827f.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"210\" height=\"298\" /></p>\n<p>Hope this helps!<br />\nMark</p><aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/2X/9/9d1d3e457f5459e3b7ca4dcf0f24b619c2e390a1.png\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" />\n\n      <a href=\"https://www.greenllamas.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Green Llamas</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    \n\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.greenllamas.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">monday.com + Green Llamas</a></h3>\n\n  <p>Green Llamas is here to help you make all your People and Projects Green.  Let us get your herds under control using the monday.com platform.</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div></div>\n</aside>\n"
